"6:124:26" : {s: 6, a: 124, w: 26, r: "شدد", t: "شَدِيدٌۢ", l: "شَدِيد", lc: 56, tl: "shadīdun", lb: "কড়া",e: "severe", b: "কঠিন", i: "yang sangat pedih", f: 12, rm: "to bind tightly, strap, strengthen firmly, run, establish, make firm, hard, strong, be advanced (day), be intense. ushdud - harden, strengthen. shadiid (pl. shidaad & ashiddau - great, firm, strict, vehement, strong, violent, severe, mighty, terrible, stern, grievous, miserly, niggardly. (adj. of the forms faiil and fiaal are used indifferently for both m. and f.): ashuddun: age of full strength, maturity. ishtadda (vb. 8) - to act with violence, become hard."},
